<subSubSection id="C37D656C7448FFE6C4E8FE4CFC089C66" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD836E77448FFE6C4E8FE4CFC089C66" blockId="7.[174,1233,319,634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
Diagnosis. Both sexes distinctly differ from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647448FFE6C745FE4CFBE39FE5" box="[846,1072,479,505]" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57448FFE6C745FE4CFC069FE5" box="[846,981,479,505]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Orthonevra</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by black legs with pale knees only (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627448FFE6C5B0FE6CFD449C06" box="[443,663,511,538]" captionStart="Figs 21–26" captionStartId="6.[166,205,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[166,1224,577,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-163@6.[166,1225,576,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 21–26. Orthonevra erythrogona, male (figs 21–23) and female (figs 24–26): 21, 24 — habitus, dorsal view; 22, 25 — head, lateral view; 23, 26 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377553/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">figs 21, 22, 24, 25</figureCitation>
) (in other species, legs either entirely black or tibia pale in basal third and at apex). 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D647448FFE6C656FD8CFCA49C25" baseAuthorityName="Malm" baseAuthorityYear="1863" box="[605,887,543,569]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Orthonevra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erythrogona">
<emphasis id="B913EAF57448FFE6C656FD8CFCA49C25" box="[605,887,543,569]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">Orthonevra erythrogona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from species with bicolor legs by the basoflagellomere 2 times as long as wide (
<figureCitation id="135C2A627448FFE6C788FDACFB859C46" box="[899,1110,575,602]" captionStart="Figs 21–26" captionStartId="6.[166,205,1802,1824]" captionTargetBox="[166,1224,577,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-163@6.[166,1225,576,1778]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs 21–26. Orthonevra erythrogona, male (figs 21–23) and female (figs 24–26): 21, 24 — habitus, dorsal view; 22, 25 — head, lateral view; 23, 26 — head, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377553/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="24">figs 22, 23, 25, 26</figureCitation>
) (in other species with bicolor legs, basoflagellomere 3–4 times as long as wide).
</paragraph>
